  "text": "The substitution mapping requires a model of sequence evolution and a phylogenetic tree to work with. Several works have shown that this procedure is robust to the input model of sequence evolution (see, for instance, [CITATION_1] . We therefore fitted a Tamura (1992) (respectively [CITATION_2] homogeneous model for the ribosomal RNA (rRNA) (respectively codon) data set and estimated all numerical parameters, that is, kappa, theta Efficient Selection of Branch-Specific Models of Sequence Evolution • doi:10.1093/molbev/mss059 MBE (respectively omega), and branch lengths. These parameters were then used for mapping substitutions. For the rRNA data set, substitution mapping was performed on a rooted tree as nonstationary models will be used in the model selection procedure.",
